Figure 5a illustrates the optical reflectance spectrum of 4 wt% Cr–ZnO and Ni–CdO nanoparticles. The reflectance spectra have been recorded in the wavelength range 200–800 nm at room temperature. The reflectance spectrum has been used to derive the optical bandgaps of 4 wt% Cr–ZnO and Ni–CdO nanoparticles. The diffused reflectance of Cr–ZnO and Ni–CdO nanocrystals are analyzed by Kubelka–Munk relation:2[F(R)]=(1-R)2/2R\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
